attacks.name: Lava Plume
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Violent Finale
attacks.text: Discard all [R] Energy from this Pokémon, and put a Fusion Forte Marker on each of your opponent’s Evolution Pokémon. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Salandit

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Sizzle Swipe
attacks.text: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Jynx

abilities.name: Elemental Shift
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may move a Forte Marker from 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon to another 1 of their Pokémon.

attacks.name: Continuous Slap
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

name: Prinplup

attacks.name: Aqua Shower
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent’s Pokémon. __(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)__

attacks.name: Brine
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. __(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)__

flavorText: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.

name: Empoleon

attacks.name: Recall
attacks.text: Choose an attack from 1 of this Pokémon’s previous Evolutions and use it as this attack.

attacks.name: Ice Wing
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks __(after applying Weakness and Resistance).__

flavorText: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.

name: Frillish

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Legend has it that the residents of a sunken ancient city changed into these Pokémon.

name: Jellicent

abilities.name: Soul Transfer
abilities.text: When 1 of your Pokémon with a Forte Marker on it is Knocked Out, you may move a Forte Marker from that Pokémon to 1 of your other Pokémon. If you do, put 3 damage counters on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Mesmerize
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.

name: Cryogonal

abilities.name: Glacio Overclock
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may put a Glacio Forte Marker on 2 of your Pokémon. If you use this Ability, this Pokémon is Knocked Out. You can’t use more than 1 Glacio Overclock  Ability each turn.

attacks.name: Freeze-Dry
attacks.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a [W] Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: When the weather gets hot, these Pokémon turn into water vapor. Cryogonal are almost never seen during summer.

attacks.name: Anger Strike
attacks.text: If you didn't use Cramarant's Gup Up Ability this turn, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Corkscrew Dive
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémonwith 1 of your Benched Pokémon

name: Flaaffy

attacks.name: Discharge
attacks.text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won't grow.

name: Toxel
flavorText: This selfish, attention-seeking Pokémon stores poison and electricity in two different sacs inside its body.

name: Gastly

attacks.name: Shadow Drop
attacks.text: Put 1 damage counter on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.

name: Haunter

attacks.name: Mumble
attacks.text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Shadow Bind
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

flavorText: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

name: Gengar

abilities.name: Cursed Call
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on this Pokémon.  If you do, during this turn, attacks used by your [P] Pokémon do 20 more damage to your opponent’s Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Shadow Wave
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t use Shadow Wave.

flavorText: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

name: Hypno

attacks.name: Counter Trance
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack __(even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out)__, the Attacking Pokémon is now Alseep.

flavorText: The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum in a Hypno's hand lull the foe into deep hypnosis. While searching for prey, it polishes the pendulum.

name: Inkay

abilities.name: Light Retreat
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any [P] Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

flavorText: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

name: Indeedee

attacks.name: Graceful Growth
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Healing Hand
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: In search of happy feelings—such as joy and gratitude—Indeedee bustles around, taking diligent care of people and other Pokémon.

name: Gholdengo

abilities.name: Will of Fortune
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon, move up to 2 [P] Energy cards from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Make It Rain
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards. If this Pokémon has a Fusion, Electro or Havoc Forte Marker on it, draw 2 more cards.

flavorText: It has a sturdy body made up of stacked coins. Gholdengo overwhelms its enemies by firing coin after coin at them in quick succession.

name: Paldean Wooper

attacks.name: Find a Home
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It's dangerous for Wooper to travel alone. They line up in groups of three or four and help each other as they walk around the wetlands.

name: Paldean Clodsire

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Bog Boggle
attacks.text: If there is no Stadium in play, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It lives at the bottom of ponds and swamps. It will carry Wooper on its back and ferry them across water from one shore to the other.

name: Larvitar

attacks.name: Eat Soil
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent’s deck.

flavorText: It is born deep underground. It can't emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.

name: Pupitar

attacks.name: Devour Soil
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent’s deck.

flavorText: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

name: Tyranitar

abilities.name: Sand Stream
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may discard the top card of your opponent’s deck.

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: This attack also does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon __(both yours and your opponent’s). (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)__

flavorText: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.

attacks.name: Rapid-Fire Combat
attacks.text: Discard up to 4 Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 40 more damage for each Energy discarded in this way.

attacks.name: To the Horizon
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, this attack does 60 more damage. For each tails, put a Fusion Forte Marker on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Gallade

attacks.name: Powerful Storm
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to both Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Oracle Cut
attacks.text: You may turn as many of your face-down Prize cards face up as you like. If you do, this attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card you turned in this way. (Those Prize cards remain face up for the rest of the game.)

flavorText: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

name: Minior

attacks.name: Shooting Star
attacks.text: This attack can be used even if this Pokémon is on the Bench.

attacks.name: Self-Destruct
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 80 damage to itself.

flavorText: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

attacks.name: Powder Pursuit
attacks.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. Put an Electro Forte Marker on the new Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Pollen Hazard
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Burned, Confused and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Sycamore Slam
attacks.text: ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Garbodor

abilities.name: Virulent Odor
abilities.text: Both Active Pokémon have no Abilities, except for Virulent Odor.

attacks.name: Sludge Bomb
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.

abilities.name: Glacial Gauntlet
abilities.text: This Pokémon can use the attacks of Pokémon on your Bench with Glacio Forte Markers on them. __(You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)__

attacks.name: Tundra Wing
attacks.text: Put a Glacio Forte Marker on 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fortune's Favor
attacks.text: ==Draw a card for each Glacio Forte Marker in play __(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Ferroseed

attacks.name: Thorny Body
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

flavorText: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: Klink

attacks.name: Gear Grind
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

flavorText: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

name: Ralts
flavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.

name: Kirlia

attacks.name: Fairy Steps
attacks.text: Draw a card for each [Y] Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

abilities.name: Spectro Dance
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may put a Spectro Forte Marker on 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Star Arrow
attacks.text: ==This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon for each [Y] Energy attached to all of your Pokémon. __(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) (You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Mawile

attacks.name: Clamp
attacks.text: Until the end of your next turn, the Defending Pokémon’s Retreat Cost is [C] more.

attacks.name: Gnarly Bite
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each [C] in your opponent’s Active Pokémon’s Retreat Cost.

flavorText: Its giant jaws are actually steel horns that transformed. It fools foes into complacency with its adorable gestures, then chomps them with its huge jaws.

name: Flabébé

attacks.name: Flower Gift
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic [Y] Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: This Flabébé rides a red flower. Immediately after birth, this Pokémon begins flying around in search of a flower it likes.

name: Floette

abilities.name: Botanical Bond
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: This Pokémon uses red wavelengths of light to pour its own energy into flowers and draw forth their latent potential.

name: Mimikyu

attacks.name: Imitate
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand. You may use the effect of a Supporter card you find there as the effect of this attack.

attacks.name: Astonish
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: A lonely Pokémon, it conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and other Pokémon.

name: Noibat

attacks.name: Hyper Wind
attacks.text: If there is an Aero Forte Marker on this Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: After nightfall, they emerge from the caves they nest in during the day. Using their ultrasonic waves, they go on the hunt for ripened fruit.

name: Noivern

abilities.name: Windstorm
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench and has an Aero Forte Marker on it, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Echo Burst
attacks.text: You may discard up to 2 Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 60 more damage for each Energy you discarded in this way.

flavorText: Flying through the darkness, it weakens enemies with ultrasonic waves that could crush stone. Its fangs finish the fight.

name: Pidgey

attacks.name: Chirp for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: Pidgeotto

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. Shuffle that Pokémon and all attached cards into their deck.

flavorText: It renders its prey immobile using well-developed claws, then carries the prey more than 60 miles to its nest.

name: Pidgeot

abilities.name: Swift Search
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 7 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck. You can’t use more than 1 Swift Search Ability each turn.

attacks.name: Quick Clutch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.

name: Porygon

abilities.name: Conversion
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may look at the top 7 cards of your deck, reveal an Item card you find there, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck. If you do, discard this Pokémon and all cards attached to it.

flavorText: Porygon is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data and entering cyberspace. This Pokémon is copy-protected so it cannot be duplicated by copying.

name: Porygon2

abilities.name: Conversion2
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. If you do, discard this Pokémon and all cards attached to it.

attacks.name: Scan Again
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

flavorText: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.

name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Conversion-Z
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for up to 2 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. If you do, discard this Pokémon and all cards attached to it.

flavorText: A faulty update was added to its programming. Its behavior is noticeably strange, so the experiment may have been a failure.

name: Audino

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

name: Wooloo
flavorText: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

name: Dubwool

attacks.name: Super Charge
attacks.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by any effects on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

name: Potion
rules: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Resonance Potion
rules: Remove all Forte Markers from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Evosoda
rules: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of
your Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon. __(This__
__counts as evolving that Pokémon.)__ Shuffle your deck
afterward. You can’t use this card during your first
turn or on a Pokémon that was put into play this
turn.

name: Switch
rules: Switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched
Pokémon.

name: Fishing Rod
rules: Shuffle up to 3 in any combination of Pokémon and
Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your
deck.

name: Verina
rules: Heal 120 damage from 1 of your Pokémon. If you do,
discard all Energy from that Pokémon.

name: Poké Ball Factory
rules: Once during each player’s turn, that player may search
their deck for an Item card that has “Ball” in its
name, reveal it, and put it into their hand. Then, that
player shuffles their deck.

name: Pokémon Center
rules: Once during each player's turn, that player may remove
a Forte Marker from 1 of their Pokémon in play. If they
do, that player discards an Energy attached to that
Pokémon.

name: Technical Machine:  Tacet Distortion
rules: The Pokémon __**Forte**__ this card is attached to can use
the attack on this card. __(You still need the necessary__
__Energy to use this attack.)__ If this card is attached to 1
of your Pokémon, discard it at the end of your turn.

attacks.name: Tacet Distortion
attacks.text:
Discard all Energy cards attached to each other
   Pokémon __**Forte**__ in play.

name: Elemental Energy
rules: This card provides [C] Energy.
As long as this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides [G], [R], and [W] Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time.

name: Seedot

attacks.name: Fall of the Acorn
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard a [G] Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It hangs off branches and absorbs nutrients. When it finishes eating, its body becomes so heavy that it drops to the ground with a thump.

name: Nuzleaf

attacks.name: Wood Whistle
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Branch Break
attacks.text: Discard a [G] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: A forest-dwelling Pokémon that is skilled at climbing trees. Its long and pointed nose is its weak point. It loses power if the nose is gripped.

name: Shiftry

attacks.name: Feint Attack
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Leafy Fans
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon. If you discarded any Energy in this way, your opponent shuffles their Active Pokémon and all attached cards into their deck.

flavorText: Shiftry's large fans generate awesome gusts of wind at a speed close to 100 feet per second. The whipped-up wind blows anything away. This Pokémon chooses to live quietly deep in forests.

name: Volbeat

attacks.name: Acrobatics
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Firefly Lights
attacks.text: If you have Illumise in play, this attack can be used even if this Pokémon is on the Bench. Both Active Pokémon are now Burned and Confused.

flavorText: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise's sweet aroma.

name: Illumise

abilities.name: Aroma Signal
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if you have Volbeat in play, you may use this Ability. Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon that has 40 HP or less remaining to the Active Spot.

attacks.name: Soothing Scent
attacks.text: This Pokémon recovers from all Special Conditions.

flavorText: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

abilities.name: Ominous Tablets
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and has a [D] Energy attached, your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost is [C] more.

attacks.name: Phantom Etching
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage for each [G] and [D] Energy attached to this Pokémon. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Vulpix

attacks.name: Tail Whip
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t attack.

flavorText: It controls balls of fire. As it grows, its six tails split from their tips to make more tails.

name: Ninetales

abilities.name: Wisping Spell
abilities.text: You must discard an Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may make both Active Pokémon Burned.

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its nine tails are said to be imbued with a mystic power. It can live for a thousand years.

name: Turtonator

attacks.name: Flame Shot
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon for each [R] Energy attached to this Pokémon. __(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)__

attacks.name: Inferno Onrush
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: Its exploding shell poses a real danger but is sensitive to moisture. On rainy days, Turtonator takes silent refuge in caves.

abilities.name: Ominous Eyes
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and has a [D] Energy attached, this Pokémon's attacks do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Burning Jealousy
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each damage counter on both Active Pokémon. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Delibird

attacks.name: Present
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. If 1 of them is heads, put 2 damage counters on your opponent’s Active Pokémon. If 2 of them are heads, put 4 damage counters on your opponent’s Active Pokémon. If all of them are heads, put 6 damage counters on your opponent’s Active Pokémon. If all of them are tails, heal 60 damage from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.

name: Lotad

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Swimming
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon lives in ponds with clean water. It is known to ferry small Pokémon across ponds by carrying them on the broad leaf on its head.

name: Lombre

attacks.name: Aqua Feed
attacks.text: Search your deck for an Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Bubble Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: In the evening, it takes great delight in popping out of rivers and startling people. It feeds on aquatic moss that grows on rocks in the riverbed.

name: Ludicolo

abilities.name: Aqua Tempo
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Basic [W] Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Rejuvenating Dance
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any [G] Energy attached, heal 40 damage from it.

flavorText: When it hears festive music, all the cells in its body become stimulated, and it begins moving in rhythm. It does not quail even when it faces a tough opponent.

name: Feebas

attacks.name: Scurry Away
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's turn.

flavorText: This tough Pokémon is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn't popular.

name: Milotic

abilities.name: Tides of Myst
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if you have Black Shores in play, you may draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Light Pulse
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It is the world’s most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.

name: Clamperl

attacks.name: Hardened Gift
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), you may draw 3 cards.

flavorText: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.

name: Huntail

attacks.name: Crashing Bite
attacks.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, put damage counters on it until its remaining HP is 30. If you placed any damage counters in this way, discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

name: Gorebyss

attacks.name: Vitality Feed
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, Evolution Pokémon in play __(both yours and your opponent’s)__ have no Abilities. __(This includes new Pokémon that come into play.)__

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.

abilities.name: Ominous Blades
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and has a [D] Energy attached, this Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks __(before applying Weakness and Resistance)__.

attacks.name: Glacial Gaze
attacks.text: Discard any number of Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 70 damage for each Energy discarded in this way. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Magnemite

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

name: Magneton

abilities.name: Magnetic Field
abilities.text: You must discard an Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may put up to 2 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand, except for the Energy card you discarded to use this Ability.

flavorText: The stronger electromagnetic waves from the three linked Magnemite are enough to dry out surrounding moisture.

attacks.name: Sparking Flash
attacks.text: Discard any number of [L] Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 30 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Forever Seeking
attacks.text: ==__You may put an Electro Forte Marker on this Pokémon. If you do, you may search your deck for 3 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Lanturn

attacks.name: Tidal Cleanse
attacks.text: You may remove a Forte Marker from either Active Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Conduct Lightning
attacks.text: When using this attack, Weakness is counted as x3.

flavorText: Portions of its dorsal fin mutated, becoming the parts that glow brightly to lure prey.

name: Stunfisk

attacks.name: Tricky Snap
attacks.text: Until the Defending Pokémon leaves the Active Spot, its Weakness is now [L]. (The amount of Weakness doesn’t change.)

attacks.name: Thunder Cure
attacks.text: Remove a Forte Marker on this Pokémon.

flavorText: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

name: #ERROR!

attacks.name: Clear Ice
attacks.text: Look at your face-down Prize cards.

attacks.name: Psy Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Its talent is tap-dancing. It can also manipulate temperatures to create a floor of ice, which this Pokémon can kick up to use as a barrier.

name: Galarian Mr. Rime

abilities.name: Star Dancer
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may switch the top card of your deck with 1 of your Prize cards. __(Put the new Prize card face down.)__ You can’t use more than 1 Star Dancer Ability during your turn.

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: Discard 2 [P] Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

name: Woobat

attacks.name: Dual Draw
attacks.text: Each player draws 2 cards.

attacks.name: Small Gust
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

name: Swoobat

abilities.name: Devotion Draw
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may draw cards until you have 4 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Air Cutter
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.

name: Honedge

attacks.name: Gouge
attacks.text: Put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon that has damage on it.

flavorText: The blue eye on the sword’s handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people’s lives away.

name: Doublade

attacks.name: Double the Pain
attacks.text: Double the number of damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

attacks.name: Shadow Blade
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has a Havoc Forte Marker on it, ignore the effects of that Forte Marker, and this attack also does 80 more damage.

attacks.name: Power Shift
attacks.text: For the rest of the game, attacks used by your Pokémon do 30 more damage to your opponent's Pokemon. __==(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)==__

name: Bruxish

attacks.name: Chasing Jaws
attacks.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. This attack does 20 damage to the new Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It burrows beneath the sand, radiating psychic power from the protuberance on its head. It waits for prey as it surveys the area.

name: Hatenna

attacks.name: Teleport
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: If this Pokémon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.

name: Hatterene

attacks.name: Draining Grudge
attacks.text: Put 1 damage counter on your opponent’s Active Pokémon for each Basic [P] Energy card in your discard pile.

attacks.name: Terror Tear
attacks.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

flavorText: If you're too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Forest Witch.

name: Sudowoodo

attacks.name: Dry Strike
attacks.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a [W] Pokémon, this attack does 20 less damage.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.

name: Flamigo

attacks.name: Dancing Flock
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon in play that has “Flamigo" in its name (both yours and your opponent’s).

flavorText: Thanks to a behavior of theirs known as "synchronizing," an entire flock of these Pokémon can attack simultaneously in perfect harmony.

abilities.name: Ominous Vessel
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has a [D] Energy attached, its Retreat Cost is [C] less.

attacks.name: Ground Crusher
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Purified Ruin
attacks.text: Put 9 damage counters on each Pokémon in play __(both yours and your opponent's)__ that doesn't have a [D] Energy attached. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Nidoran [+]

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging, they'll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.

name: Nidorina

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: The horn on its head has atrophied. It's thought that this happens so Nidorina's children won't get poked while their mother is feeding them.

name: Nidoqueen

attacks.name: Epiphyte Quake
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Blake Blight
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your deck. If it is a [D] Energy card, this attack does 30 more damage and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.

attacks.name: Stagger Claw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, Put an Electro Forte Marker on your opponent’s Active Pokémon. If tails, Put an Electro Forte Marker on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Judgement Strike
attacks.text: This attack does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon that has any Forte Markers on it. ==__(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) (You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Zorua

attacks.name: Ascension
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It changes so it looks just like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.

name: Zoroark

abilities.name: Deceptive Draw
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a card for each of your Benched Pokémon that has any [D] Energy attached.  You can’t use more than 1 Deceptive Draw Ability during your turn.

flavorText: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

name: Skarmory

attacks.name: Havoc Beam
attacks.text: This attack ignores the effects of Forte Markers on both Active Pokémon. If either Active Pokémon has a Havoc Forte Marker on it, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: Its sturdy, heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.

name: Galarian Perrserker

attacks.name: Berserking Discord
attacks.text: You may put a Fusion Forte Marker on the Defending Pokémon. If you do, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Axe Now
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, put a Trainer card from your discard pile back into your hand.

flavorText: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

name: Galarian Stunfisk

attacks.name: Sharp Traps
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage for each [C] in all of your opponent’s Pokémon’s Retreat Cost.

flavorText: Its conspicuous lips lure prey in as it lies in wait in the mud. When prey gets close, Stunfisk clamps its jagged steel fins down on them.

name: Cottonee

attacks.name: Cotton Guard
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage done to this  Pokémon by attacks.

flavorText: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that’s highly prized by many luxury brands.

name: Whimsicott

abilities.name: Miracle Wind
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may discard a [Y] Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, put a Spectro Forte Marker on 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Brilliant Shot
attacks.text: This Pokémon recovers from all Special Conditions.

flavorText: It rides on the wind and slips into people’s homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton-filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.

name: Spritzee

attacks.name: Sweet Scent
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

flavorText: A scent pouch within this Pokémon's body allows it to create various scents. A change in its diet will alter the fragrance it produces.

name: Aromatisse

abilities.name: Scented Wish
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Starshine Moonblast
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has a Forte Marker on it, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: The scent that constantly emits from its fur is so powerful that this Pokémon's companions will eventually lose their sense of smell.

name: Druddigon

attacks.name: Revenge
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent’s last turn, this attack does 70 more damage.

attacks.name: Sunbathing
attacks.text: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon and heal 70 damage from it.

flavorText: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.

name: Slakoth

attacks.name: Lazy Yawn
attacks.text: Both Active Pokémon are now Asleep.

flavorText: Slakoth's heart beats just once a minute. Whatever happens, it is content to loaf around motionless. It is rare to see this Pokémon in motion.

name: Snorlax

abilities.name: Thick Fat
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks from your opponent’s [R] or [W] Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Devouring
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you may discard any number of Pokémon Tools from your Pokémon. Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon for each card you discarded in this way.

flavorText: When its belly is full, it becomes too lethargic to even lift a finger, so it is safe to bounce on its belly.

name: Slaking

abilities.name: Dire Destruction
abilities.text: This Pokémon can’t attack unless it is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Facade
attacks.text: If this Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this Pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.

name: Vigoroth

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Adrenaline Rush
attacks.text: This attack can be used even if this Pokémon is Asleep or Paralyzed.

flavorText: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

name: Slaking

abilities.name: Dire Destruction
abilities.text: This Pokémon can’t attack unless it is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Facade
attacks.text: If this Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this Pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.

name: Hisuian Zorua

attacks.name: Cursed Cut
attacks.text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.

name: Hisuian Zoroark

attacks.name: Spectral Ambush
attacks.text: Discard all Special Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Bond Breaker
attacks.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Pokémon **__Forte__**, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark's own body.

name: Drampa Forte

attacks.name: Roaring Winds
attacks.text: Discard your hand and draw 6 cards.

attacks.name: Windqueller
attacks.text: You may remove an Aero Forte marker from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 80 more damage.

attacks.name: Cloud Nine
attacks.text: Move any number of Basic Energy from your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like. __==(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)==__

flavorText: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that’s highly prized by many luxury brands.

name: Full Heal
rules: Your Active Pokémon recovers from all Special
Conditions.

name: Basic Revival Inhaler
rules: Put a Basic Pokémon from your discard pile onto your
Bench.

name: Crushing Hammer
rules: You can only use 1 Crushing Hammer card in a turn.
Flip a coin. If heads, discard a Basic Energy from your
opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Startling Megaphone
rules: You can only use 1 Startling Megaphone card in a turn.
Flip a coin.  If heads, during your opponent's next turn,
attacks used by your opponent's Active Pokémon cost
[C] more.

name: Sanhua
rules: Search your deck for a Supporter card and a Stadium card, reveal them, and put them in your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Jianxin's Grounding Technique
rules: Choose up to 2 in any combination of Pokémon Tool
cards and Stadium cards __(yours or your opponent's)__
and discard them.

name: Lostlorn Forest
rules: Once during each player’s turn, that player may
choose a Pokémon that has “Zoroark” in its name in
their discard pile and switch it with 1 of their
Pokémon that has “Zoroark” in its name in play. Any
attached cards, damage counters, Special Conditions,
turns in play, Forte Markers and any other effects
remain on the new Pokémon.

name: Technical Machine: Paradox Shift
rules: The Pokémon this card is attached to can use the
attack on this card. __(You still need the necessary__
__Energy to use this attack.)__ If this card is attached to 1
of your Pokémon, discard it at the end of your turn.

attacks.name: Paradox Shift
attacks.text:
Put a Forte Marker of your choice on a Pokemon in
  play that already has a Forte Marker on it.

name: Feebas

attacks.name: Scurry Away
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's turn.

flavorText: This tough Pokémon is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn't popular.

name: Bulbasaur

attacks.name: Poison powder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: For some time after its birth, it uses the nutrients that are packed into the seed on its back in order to grow.

name: Ivysaur

attacks.name: Spread Pollen
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by any Special Conditions, or if it has any Forte Markers on it, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: The bulb on its back grows as it absorbs nutrients. The bulb gives off a pleasant armoa when it blooms.

abilities.name: Amplifying Pollen
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Poisoned Pokémon with Forte Markers on them instead of 1.

attacks.name: Poisonous Vines
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Shuckle

attacks.name: Berry Picking
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completly still.

name: Leafeon

attacks.name: Sprouting Leaf
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved during this turn, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Botanic Blade
attacks.text: Put a Basic Energy card from your discard pile back into your hand.

flavorText: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.

name: Phantump
flavorText: This Pokémon came to be when the spirit of a deceased child possessed a tree stump. It now wanders the forest searching for friends.

name: Trevenant

attacks.name: Forest's Miasma
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Forte Marker on your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Jungle Hammer
attacks.text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

flavorText: Trevenant is very kind to pokemon living in the forest. It does't even care if these Pokemon take up residen in the greenery of its head.

name: Cutiefly

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Cutiefly can pick up the auras of living things. It skillfully reads those auras to predict its foes' movements and make fools of them.

abilities.name: Sweet Gather
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for an Energy card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Starflower Blooms
attacks.text: Put a Spectro Forte Marker on each of your Benched Pokémon that have any damage counters on them. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Gossifleur

attacks.name: Twin Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

name: Eldegoss

attacks.name: Drift Away
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Seed Bomb
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

name: Magmar

attacks.name: Flame Spit
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather’s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Flareon

attacks.name: Fusion Flames
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved during this turn, you may put a Fusion Forte Marker on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Torchic

attacks.name: Run Around
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It has a flame sac inside its belly that perpetually burns. It feels warm if it is hugged.

name: Combusken

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It boosts its concentration by emitting harsh cries. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

name: Blaziken

abilities.name: Firestarter
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a [R] Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fire Stream
attacks.text: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon. This attack also does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. __(Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)__

flavorText: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.

name: Litwick

abilities.name: Singe
abilities.text: Fire

attacks.name: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Its flame is unsually out, but it starts shining when Litwick absorbs life-force from people or pokemon.

attacks.name: Eerie Flames
attacks.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Chandelure

abilities.name: Fusion Soul
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, put 2 damage counters on each Pokémon with a Fusion Forte Marker on it __(both yours and your opponents)__.

flavorText: It absorbs spirits, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: Salazzle

attacks.name: Ignite
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic [R] Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Disorienting Breath
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent’s Active Pokémon’s attacks. That Pokémon can’t use that attack during your opponent’s next turn.

flavorText: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

name: Magikarp

abilities.name: Hidden Underwater
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon from attacks __(both yours and your opponent's)__.

attacks.name: Big Splash
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokemon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

attacks.name: Furious Impact
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 40 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Tyrant's Tantrum Forte
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you amy put a Havoc Forte Marker on both Active Pokemon

name: Vaporeon

attacks.name: Glacio Burst
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved during this turn, you may put a Glacio Forte Marker on it

attacks.name: Bubble Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

name: Piplup

attacks.name: Cold Peck
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Reckless Waddle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.

name: Glaceon

attacks.name: Frost Spear
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved during this turn, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

abilities.name: Gulp Up
abilities.text: You must discard 1 of your Benched Arrokuda in order to use this ability. Once during your turn, you may heal 50 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spit Out
attacks.text: You may put any number of Arrokuda from your discard pile onto your Bench. This attack does 30 damage for each Pokemon put onto your Bench in this way.

name: Arrokuda

attacks.name: Flip Turn
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémonwith 1 of your Benched Pokémon

flavorText: After it's eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That's when Cramorant swallows it up.

name: Electabuzz

attacks.name: Thunder Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Electricity runs across the surface of its body. In darkness, its entire body glows a whitish-blue.

attacks.name: Thunder Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Electro Impact
attacks.text: Put an Electro Forte Marker on up to 3 Pokémon in play. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game).__==

name: Jolteon

attacks.name: Electro Spark
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved during this turn, you may put an Electro Forte Marker on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Bright Thunder
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: If agitated, it uses electricity to straighten out its fur and launch it in small bunches.

name: Mareep

abilities.name: Fluffy
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Static Wool
attacks.text: This attack also does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

name: Ampharos

abilities.name: Beacon of Light
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Connecting Bolt
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

name: Toxtricity

attacks.name: Electro Overdrive
attacks.text: Put 6 damage counters on each Pokémon with an Electro Forte Marker on them __(both yours and your opponent's)__.

flavorText: The jolts of electricity it launches by violently strumming the protrusions on its chest easily exceed 15,000 volts.

name: Drowzee

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that a Drowzee is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.

name: Espeon

attacks.name: Spectro Wave
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved during this turn, you may put a Spectro Forte Marker on it.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is predicting its opponent’s next move.

name: Cresselia

attacks.name: Moonlight Blessing
attacks.text: Remove all Fusion, Electro, and Havoc Forte Markers from each of your Pokémon in play.

attacks.name: Crescent Beam
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

attacks.name: Heated Hypnosis
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent’s last turn, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Illusion Collapse
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, put a Havoc Forte Marker on 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. ==__(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)__==

name: Gimmighoul

attacks.name: Coin Collector
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic [P] Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes it’s actually a Pokémon.

name: Onix

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Collaspe
attacks.text: Discard the top card from both players' decks.

flavorText: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It knows how people and Pokémon feel by looking at their auras. It doesn't approach dangerous opponents.

name: Lucario

attacks.name: Resonation
attacks.text: Choose an attack from any Pokémon __**Forte**__ in play and use it as this attack. (You cannot choose __**Forte**__ attacks in this way.)

flavorText: It concentrates its mental energy and fires off mysterious waves called auras, which can crush boulders of large size to dust.

name: Falinks

abilities.name: Call for Backup
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon __(even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out)__, you may search your deck for a Pokémon that has “Falinks” in its name and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: All Out Attack
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Falinks in play.

flavorText: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.

name: Nidoran ♂

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: The horn on a male Nidoran's forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

name: Nidorino

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads

flavorText: With a horn that's harder than diamond, this Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.

name: Nidoking

abilities.name: Havoc Overload
abilities.text: Once during either player's turn, whenever either player puts a Forte Marker on this Pokémon, draw a card.

attacks.name: Revenge Kill
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Forte Marker on both Active Pokémon.

flavorText: When it goes on a rampage, it's impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it's lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

name: Umbreon

attacks.name: Moonlit Havoc
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved during this turn, put a Havoc Forte Marker on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: When exposed to the moon’s aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.

name: Sableye

attacks.name: Gem Search
attacks.text: Look at the top card of your deck. You may put that card into your hand. If you don’t, discard that card and draw a card.

attacks.name: Crazy Claws
attacks.text: If neither Active Pokémon have any Forte Markers on them, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It feeds on gemstone crystals. In darkness, its eyes sparkle with the glitter of jewels.

name: Trubbish

attacks.name: Poison Gas
attacks.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Trashalanche
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Item card in your opponent’s discard pile.

flavorText: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokémon.

abilities.name: Distortion Gate Forte
abilities.text: For each different kind of Forte Marker, choose a Pokémon in play. Put a Forte Marker of that kind on that Pokémon. (You cannot use more than 1 Forte attack in a game)

attacks.name: Dimensional Hands
attacks.text: Put 10 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon with a Forte Marker on it.

attacks.name: Foundry Drive
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon __(even if it's Knocked Out)__, put a Havoc Forte Marker on the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fortified Impact
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 100 less damage from attacks __(before applying Weakness and Resistance)__. __==(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)==__

name: Beldum

attacks.name: Learn
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground's natural magnetism, letting it float.

name: Metang

attacks.name: Scanning Algorithm
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards. If you do, discard a card from your hand.

attacks.name: Heavy Impact
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.

name: Metagross

abilities.name: Supercompute
abilities.text: You must remove a Glacio, Aero, or Spectro Forte Marker from this Pokémon in order to use this ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards. You can't use more than 1 Supercompute ability each turn.

attacks.name: Gigaton Impact
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 40 damage to itself.

flavorText: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokémon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.

name: Ferrothorn

attacks.name: Thorny Body
attacks.text: During your opponent’s next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon equal to the damage done to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spike Cannon
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

name: Klang

attacks.name: Gear Grind
attacks.text: Flip 5 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Full Body Impact
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 60 damage to itself.

flavorText: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon’s rotation speed increases sharply.

name: Klinklang

attacks.name: Gear Smash
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each of your Benched Pokémon with Forte Markers on them. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

flavorText: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

name: Genesect

attacks.name: Destructor Cannon
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Special Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

name: Florges

attacks.name: Wither Once Again
attacks.text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.

attacks.name: Blossoming Barrage
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon has a Spectro Forte Marker on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: They say that flower gardens created by Florges are constantly showered with a power that can heal both body and spirit.

name: Sylveon

attacks.name: Aero Ribbon
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved during this turn, you may put an Aero Forte Marker on this Pokémon.

flavorText: Sylveon cuts an elegant figure as it dances lightly around, feelers fluttering, but its piercing moves aim straight for its opponents’ weak spots.

name: Klefki

abilities.name: Tool for the Job
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for a Pokémon Tool card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Key Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

flavorText: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

name: Gible
flavorText: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

name: Gabite

attacks.name: Jet Headbutt
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Swift Shred
attacks.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by any effects on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from a protrusion on either side of its head to probe pitch-dark caves.

attacks.name: Sudden Strike
attacks.text: If this Pokemon was on your Bench and became your Active Pokémon this turn, this attack does 100 more damage.

attacks.name: Sonic Dive
attacks.text: Put an Aero Forte Marker on up to 2 of your Pokémon in play. __==(You can't use more than 1 **Forte** attack in a game.)==__

attacks.name: Mimicry Forte
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon Forte's attacks and use it as this attack. (You can choose Forte Attacks in this way.)(You can't use more than 1 Forte Attack in a game.)

name: Eevee

attacks.name: Veeveelution
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It can evolve into a variety of forms. Eevee's genes are the key to solving the mysteries of Pokémon evolution.

name: Squawkabilly

attacks.name: Early Flocking
attacks.text: If you go first, you can use this attack during your first turn. Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Fury Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

flavorText: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

name: Poké Ball
rules: Search your deck for a Pokémon with 80 HP or less,
reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your
deck.

name: Great Ball
rules: Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. You may reveal
a Pokémon you find there and put it into your hand.
Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Ultra Ball
rules: You can use this card only if you discard 2 other cards
from your hand.
Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it
into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Forte Examination Report
rules: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards of
different types, reveal them, and put them into your
hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Jiyan
rules: Draw 3 cards.

name: Baizhi
rules: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 5 cards.

name: Professor's Research
rules: Discard your hand and draw 7 cards.

name: Brant
rules: Reveal a Pokémon from your hand and put it into
your deck. If you do, search your deck for a Pokémon,
reveal it, and put into your hand.Then, shuffle your
deck.

name: Youhu
rules: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon, reveal
them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle
your deck.

name: Hex Maniac
rules: You can use this card only if you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent.
Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.

name: Black Shores
rules: Once during each player’s turn, that player may look
at the top 3 cards of their deck and put them back
in any order.

name: Warp Portal
rules: Once during each player’s turn, that player may move
a Basic Energy from 1 of their Pokémon to another
of their Pokémon.

name: Angelica Tea
rules: At the end of each turn, if the Pokémon this card is
attached to has 3 or more damage counters on it,
heal 30 damage from it and discard this card.

name: Jinzhou Skewers
rules: If this card is attached to 1 of your Pokémon, discard
it at the end of your turn.
Attacks used by the Pokémon this card is attached
to do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active
Pokémon __(before applying Weakness and Resistance)__.
